BA in American Studies, Minor in Creative Writing{" "} • Sept 2016 - June 2020

My academics focus on questions of representation in American art and entertainment. Through my coursework, I explore the ways in which marginalized identities have been historically excluded from the American artistic canon, and how contemporary artists and storytellers can work to weave these identities back into the American imagination.

Featured Courses: Race Gender and Sexuality in Contemporary American Film, Fiction into Film (Screenwriting Seminar), Script Analysis, Fiction Writing, Dialogue Writing, Beginning Improvising, Racial Indentity in the American Imagination
